			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Language-Parametric Approach to Exploratory Programming Environments</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LThomasvanBinsbergen.html">L. Thomas van Binsbergen</a>, <a href="../profile/DamianFrölich.html">Damian Frölich</a>, <a href="../profile/MauricioVeranoMerino.html">Mauricio Verano Merino</a>, <a href="../profile/JoeyLai.html">Joey Lai</a>, <a href="../profile/PierreJeanjean.html">Pierre Jeanjean</a>, <a href="../profile/TijsvanderStorm.html">Tijs van der Storm</a>, <a href="../profile/BenoîtCombemale.html">Benoît Combemale</a>, <a href="../profile/OlivierBarais.html">Olivier Barais</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567527">10.1145/3567512.3567527</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It proposes a language-independent protocol/architecture for exploratory programming environments.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> A protocol like LSP is about integrating/coordinating language components across tools.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> The target settings (REPLs/notebooks) rely on runtime interaction and interpretation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
